ars) from Nucleotide database and high-quality metagenomes were retrieved, and then the locations of the sequences described in the literatures were searched. Numbers in columns shows numbers of searched targeted sequences including 16S rRNA genes and metagenomes. All information is listed in Supplementary Table 1 and Supplementary Table 2. A world map was drawn by Arcgis 10.5 and the information of wetland distribution including peatland was derived from https://www.worldwildlife.org/pages/global-lakes-and-wetlands-database.Extended Data Table 1 Peatland soils sampled from the Great Khingan, China and the shrub cover levelsFull size tableExtended Data Table 2 Contents of the free monophenols (mg·g−1 DW soil) in the Greater Khingan peatland soils with different shrub cover levels*Full size tableExtended Data Table 3 Conversion percentages of the carbon in added lignin or monophenols to CH4 in peatland soil microcosmsFull size tableExtended Data Table 4 Accumulation of 13C-acetate from 13C-methoxy or 13C-phenyl groups, and of 13C-propionate and 13C-iso-butyrate from 13C-phenyl groups of vanillin in peatland soil microcosm incubated at 28 °C*Full size tableExtended Data Table 5 Primers for qPCR test used in this studyFull size tableSupplementary informationSupplementary InformationSupplementary Tables 1 and 2.Source dataSource Data (all figures and tables)Statistical source data (32 worksheets, Fig. 1b, Fig. 1c, Fig. 1d; Fig. 2a upper, Fig. 2a lower, Fig. 2b upper, Fig. 2b lower, Fig. 2c upper, Fig. 2c lower, Fig. 2d upper, Fig. 2d lower, Fig. 2e upper, Fig. 2e lower; Fig. 3a, Fig. 3b, Fig. 3c, Fig. 3d; Fig. 4a left, Fig. 4a right, Fig. 4b left, Fig. 4b right, Fig. 4c left, Fig. 4c right; ED Fig. 1a, ED Fig. 1b; ED Fig. 2a left, ED Fig. 2a right, ED Fig. 2b left, ED Fig. 2b right; ED Table 2; ED Table 3; ED Table 4).Rights and permissionsSpringer Nature or its licensor (e.g. a society or other partner) holds exclusive rights to this article under a publishing agreemen